      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "URANA JAM DONUT (4) had the drop on the lead before drawing clear to score (19.81) at Angle Park in a Grade 6 over 342m. Goes well out of this box with a win and three minor placings. The one to beat again. NOVA'S FERN (2) is a capable type and proved too classy last time to win by 2.25 lengths at Angle Park in a handy 34.47 beating Legs Eleven. Should feature again. COMPTON ROCKY (8) was prominent throughout when winning two back but could manage only midfield last time when 5th and beaten 11 lengths at Mt Gambier (30.11). Can do much better this time. URANA UNO (6) hasn't been far away, finishing in the money twice in a row including last time in a Grade 6 at Angle Park over 530m.",
